## notes.txt

```txt
- Initially had networking problems due to Host-Only adapter configuration
- VM occasionally froze during scans
- Learned difference between localhost (127.0.0.1) and actual VM IP
- First exploit attempts failed because target was offline/rebooted
- Needed correct RHOSTS/LHOST configuration
- Learned how Meterpreter differs from normal shell
- Used shell command inside Meterpreter to access Linux terminal
- Took screenshots of:
  - Nmap scan
  - exploit configuration
  - successful session
  - whoami
  - uname -a

Observations:
- Enumeration is more important than blindly exploiting
- Old vulnerable systems can behave unpredictably
- Metasploit simplifies exploitation workflow but understanding the process still matters
